{"nodes": [{"id": "tickets_ticket_page", "label": "Waiter Tickets page", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The waiter-facing surface where orders are served, sent back, expedited, voided, rushed, and closed. The waiter never edits the cook plan directly; actions create kitchen work or clear it, and the scheduler reacts."}, {"id": "tickets_line_state_machine", "label": "Line state machine (open/served/void)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Three orthogonal axes kept distinct: Line.state (persistent waiter-set: open/served/void); Cooking status (derived from clock, open lines only: waiting->cooking->ready); Re-fire (persistent: reAt != null fires now with priority)."}, {"id": "tickets_ticket_state_machine", "label": "Ticket lifecycle (active/done)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A ticket is resolvable (Done without warning) once every line is served or void. A recook auto-reopens a Done ticket because there is new work."}, {"id": "tickets_cooking_status", "label": "Cooking status (derived: waiting/cooking/ready)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Cooking progress is derived from the clock and never stored; open lines flow waiting->cooking->ready on the kitchen clock as status only, no state change."}, {"id": "tickets_recook", "label": "Recook (send back)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Keeps the line open but sets reAt = now plus a reason, making the scheduler fire it immediately with priority; bumps the recook count (quality metric) and reopens a Done ticket. Requires picking a reason from RECOOK_REASONS."}, {"id": "tickets_fire_now", "label": "Fire now / expedite", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Re-fires a missing item now with no reason, shows FIRE NOW (orange), jumps the queue. Distinguished from recook by reason == null."}, {"id": "tickets_rush", "label": "Rush (ticket-level)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Toggling rush sets SLA = min(SLA[type], RUSH_SLA) and marks all the ticket's lines priority=true so the whole ticket fires sooner and shows RUSH."}, {"id": "tickets_reat", "label": "reAt / re-fire mechanism", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A line with reAt != null (recook/expedite) feeds the scheduler as target = reAt + cook (fires now) with priority = true. Priority lines sort before normal lines and never batch."}, {"id": "tickets_scheduler_contract", "label": "Scheduler contract (ticket page -> schedule())", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "The ticket page changes inputs, not the algorithm: lines with state in {served,void} are skipped; reAt != null sets target=reAt+cook and priority; rush tightens SLA and prioritises all lines; priority lines sort before normal and never batch. Capacity, batching, hold-vs-late, lane-packing unchanged."}, {"id": "tickets_two_way_loop", "label": "Two-way loop with the kitchen", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A waiter action mutates the line/ticket -> the schedule recomputes -> the kitchen views update. Serving removes kitchen work; recook/fire-now/restore/unserve add it; void removes it."}, {"id": "tickets_priority_badges", "label": "Priority badges (RECOOK / FIRE NOW / RUSH)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Kitchen views show red RECOOK\u00b7reason, orange FIRE NOW, and orange RUSH badges; re-fired/rushed items sort first on Fire-next and Stations."}, {"id": "tickets_priority_kind", "label": "Priority kind (recook vs expedite)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "reason distinguishes a recook (sent back, red badge) from an expedite/fire-missing (orange badge); reason is null on a plain expedite/fire-missing."}, {"id": "tickets_under_lamp", "label": "Under-lamp warning", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "underLamp(line) = ready and unserved for more than READY_LIMIT (4) mins - flags food sitting under the heat lamp too long."}, {"id": "tickets_rush_sla", "label": "RUSH_SLA constant", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "tickets_sync_events", "label": "Sync/audit events (ItemServed, ...)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "TICKETS.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "One 